:-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":6,"Type":"paragraph","Text":" I run 6 Al sub-agents that handle my entire content pipeline.Research, drafting,scheduling,repurposing-al of it.My total Al tooling cost is$5 a day.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":247,"Y":762},"LeftTop":{"X":247,"Y":705},"RightBottom":{"X":1128,"Y":762},"RightTop":{"X":1128,"Y":705}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":7,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"For the first 4 months I babysitted every single one of them. An agent would finish a task, forget everything it","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":247,"Y":834},"LeftTop":{"X":247,"Y":779},"RightBottom":{"X":1113,"Y":834},"RightTop":{"X":1113,"Y":779}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":8,"Type":"paragraph","Text":" The fix was not a better prompt. It was not a smarter model. It was giving my agents a place to live-a unifie virtual filesystem. Once every agent shared the same organized file structure and could read and write persistent state, the babysitting stopped. I got 80% of my research time back.The agents started finishing job without me.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":247,"Y":967},"LeftTop":{"X":247,"Y":853},"RightBottom":{"X":1131,"Y":967},"RightTop":{"X":1131,"Y":853}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":9,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"This guide shows you exactly how I set that up. No engineering degree required. You will walk away with a working file structure,3 copy-paste prompts you can use today, and a clear picture of why your current setup keeps breaking.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":247,"Y":1074},"LeftTop":{"X":247,"Y":987},"RightBottom":{"X":1116,"Y":1074},"RightTop":{"X":1116,"Y":987}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":10,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"How to use this guide","Level":0,"Polygon":{"Le